main event: A bright white light was observed circling the moon for 15 minutes in Seattle, Washington on August 13, 1965.
interesting points: The object was initially observed as another planet before it was seen circling the moon.
The object was described as a solid, white light that did not exhibit any characteristics of another planet.
The observer stated the object did not appear to be an aircraft.
The sighting lasted for approximately 15 minutes.
The sky was clear during the sighting.
